    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`util.show_document` does not handle the `external` flag: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/d0aedd36dfe0ac4ed45ea93f471379c77f0c7905/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua#L907\n\nso callers such as `handlers.lua:window_showDocument` must do it themselves: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/d0aedd36dfe0ac4ed45ea93f471379c77f0c7905/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/handlers.lua#L599-L605\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nshould `util.show_document` handle `external` ? or gain a new parameter?\n\nor should we drop `util.show_document` entirely and point plugins to `handles.lua:window_showDocument` ?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hmmm IMO the current design feels okay. `show_document` should be about showing local files in the editor. If we add an `external` argument then the other ones (`location`, the encoding and `opts`) would just be ignored since they're not applicable.",
